[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about how the macro should avoid using placeholders in string parts. There are considerations around whitespace and unicode escapes, which makes me wonder about the JSON parser. I’m also pondering if there's a way to introduce compile-time invalid checks that won’t actually compile. Maybe I can test the root scalar using string interpolation. It looks like I might need some imports, particularly for comparing JSON with no spaces or sorted keys, and using assertj. I’m curious about potential issues with public top-level case classes or objects.
